- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper compares two probabilistic data structures for association queries derived from the Bloom filter. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of the data structures with respect to false positive probability and inter-set error probability. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with probabilistic data structures and presents new probability formulas. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper discusses false positive probability and inter-set error probability, which are important in security applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with data structures for association queries, which could be relevant in AI applications.
